            <h3 data-uuid="939f3b7ac20e4ccfaf79f429e1598343">Part 2: Write an Explanatory Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="4b64573cfd344a26a5913ba52f8d8570">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="88ad60f7022949afab20026a5ecc846f">Across time, people in all world regions, have created
                maps to make sense of their place in the world and their relationships to other people and places. Such
                maps often depict features of the landscape, bodies of water, or the skies
                above. They also reveal the cultural beliefs and knowledge of the mapmakers
                who created them.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="8122f7a224c84e5eaec94d08b0bb8293">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="422818431caa47e5ac9a2d02ef94d411">What can we learn about people from the maps they
                create? Write an explanatory essay about the maps in this module and how they
                reflect cultural and geographic knowledge. In your own words, describe the
                content and purpose of each map. Be sure to tell what you think it reveals
                about beliefs and knowledge held by the mapmaker.</p>
            <p data-uuid="62de4e4d1187487ab31274827db75b71">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="6b584210247645f4aa17b5b9f0c565f6">
                <li data-uuid="4aaeb446450c48a787a7e817e2c4fe0d">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="a01bce60351740b7b86bd065a92287f1">
                    Use at least <i>three</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic
                    with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="d58a02b319f14fbfa4b75863f0f75284">
                    Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your
                    response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="19d7ed4445fd49a29bf9a4ec4939657f">Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body
                    paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="9f9776230b724afe8b70085fd4aea64f">Organize your essay in a clear way that focuses on the topic and supports it with explanations and facts.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="929946b2cf774087bc88e39891218065">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
